== Funding Options ==

Financial support can be directed at specific areas:

|=Area|=What It Covers|=Why It Matters
|**AI infrastructure**|LLM API costs (~$0.20–0.55 per analysis, target < $0.10)|Every analysis requires ~30 AI calls across multiple providers — the largest running cost
|**Search and hosting**|Web search APIs, server hosting, databases|Evidence retrieval depends on paid search APIs; hosting keeps the service available
|**Research partnerships**|Joint R&D with university partners (ZHAW cooperation open)|Academic collaboration improves quality and unlocks grant funding
|**Development**|Performance, new features (browser extensions, API, live fact-checking)|Moves FactHarbor from Alpha toward a production-ready public service
|**Operations**|Open-source maintenance, documentation, community|Keeps the project sustainable and accessible long-term

=== Funding Instruments ===

|=Instrument|=Typical Amount|=Who
|**Foundation grants**|CHF 20K–300K|Mercator, Ernst Göhner, Migros Kulturprozent, Hasler Foundation — fund specific development or research tracks
|**Innosuisse Innovation Cheque**|CHF 15,000 (100% funded)|Feasibility study with academic partner — no co-funding required
|**Innosuisse Innovation Project**|CHF 100K–500K|Joint R&D with university partner (40–60% cost split, in-kind eligible)
|**BRIDGE Proof of Concept**|Up to CHF 130K/year|Academic-led commercialization — researcher-initiated
|**International grants**|EUR 25K–300K|IFCN Global Fact Check Fund, Google News Initiative, European Media and Information Fund
|**Infrastructure sponsorship**|Varies|Cover AI or hosting costs — directly extends the number of analyses we can run
|**Individual donations**|Any amount|Direct financial contribution to development and operations

(% class="box infomessage" style="background-color:#eef3f8;border-color:#9db4cb;" %)
(((
**Every franc goes to the mission.** No profit distribution — surplus is reinvested. All funders above CHF 5,000 will be disclosed.
)))

